essentially it breaks when these two macros are used together:

note the semicolon which is missing in the macro so that you can append output with "<<" operator. When you delete it you get other types of errors on those two lines. so they affect each other 

`CHECK_EQ(unit_size_[i], d.data[i].Size());`

` MSHADOW_TYPE_SWITCH(data_[i].type_flag_, DType, {
            mshadow::Copy(
              data_[i].get<cpu, 1, DType>().Slice(top * unit_size_[i],
                                                  (top + 1) * unit_size_[i]),
              d.data[i].get_with_shape<cpu, 1, DType>(mshadow::Shape1(unit_size_[i])));
          }); `

the affected file is src/io/iter_batchloader.h on line 83 and 105

@bdlacree: Did you manage to replicate the example in R? I'm having a hard time doing so and would love to see your version if you managed to do it?

